cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a problem in computer vision, specifically cross-view classification, which involves multiple views of data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method that involves learning a common subspace for multi-view data, which falls under the category of subspace learning. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also incorporates supervised information and local geometric information, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a kernel method to boost performance, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
